<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
Leaves obovate to narrowly linear-oblanceolate, hairs strongly appressed, sometimes sericeous and clearly differentiated from the spreading hairs of the calyx. [
<bibRefCitation author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Saâ€™ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 140; 
<bibRefCitation author="Polunin, O" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford" pageId="209" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 592" refId="B278" refString="Polunin, O, 1980. Flowers of Greece and the Balkans. Oxford University Press, Oxford: 1 - 592" title="Flowers of Greece and the Balkans" year="1980">Polunin 1980</bibRefCitation>
(Plate 35)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
Balkan peninsular and Turkey: Croatia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Botteri</emphasis>
s.n.); Albania (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Alston &amp; Sandwith</emphasis>
2154); Montenegro; Macedonia (?); Bulgaria (?); Greece (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Rechinger</emphasis>
9545, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Guicciardi</emphasis>
2963); Turkey (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Balansa</emphasis>
1168, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Dudley</emphasis>
37177, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Davis</emphasis>
21878, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Post</emphasis>
528).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. compactus" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="compactus" subSpecies="compactus">Subsp. compactus</taxonomicName>
is very variable in leaf shape, plants with almost linear leaves from Turkey such as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Balls</emphasis>
1366 fit the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sa'ad" authorityYear="1967" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus konyacus" order="Solanales" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="konyacus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Convolvulus konyacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this only seems to be one extreme in the range of variation.
</paragraph>
